verbose_text: As indicated by the XPS spectra of the PdAg/C (XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY), an approximately 0.4-0.5 eV chemical shifts of the Pd 3d core level to higher bind energy were observed in the Pd 80 Ag 20 / C and Pd 65 Ag 35 / C catalysts attributed to the strong interaction between Pd and Ag atoms, which could influence the adsorption of methanol or intermediates, resulting in enhancing the electro activity XREF_BIBR.
